content: The try build CI appears to have finished, but bors didn't leave a comment: https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/pull/80689#issuecomment-778838397
I know if you push (at least force push, maybe any push) bors will no longer connect the try build with the PR, so that might be the cause - unclear on the sequence here

I think the reason was, that the "bors build finished" job for the try build just ran 2 minutes ago with a few minutes delay. bors only tracks the state of this job and only comments, if that job finished. But since there are new commits now, no comment is produced?
Yeah, it ran with a 10 minute delay, so I guess just a GH hick-up.
I pushed a commit after starting the build, so that's probably it
